</span><hr size=1> would this be a fair item for melees to have?<br>
<br>
Null Stone<br>
Lore - No drop - Magic<br>
right click: nulify enchantments<br>
cast time: 1.0 sec<br>
recast time: 30.0 sec<br>
charges: infinite<br>
<br>
<br>
The way I think this should work is when you click it, it debuffs 2 buffs like nulify, only its cast time is 1.0 seconds, as opposed to Pumice stone's ~4.5 seconds.  But to offset this speed, a built in recast time of 30 seconds is added to the item.<br>
<br>
I posted this because I don't think its fair that melees are unable to pumice off, say, a necro dot because the necro pet perma-interrupts them due to no channeling skill.  On the other hand, I don't agree with how easy it can be (with egg shaped pumice and golem wands) to totally debuff a int caster (like me) and turn him into a siting duck.  Would this item be a fair solution to the current state of debuff items in PvP? thoughts?<br>
